  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global (Kenya, Tanzania, Uganda, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka): Global RECAP: Global Regulatory &amp; Fiscal Capacity Building Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To strengthen the capacity of government officials, regulators, policymakers, research institutions and civil society to understand, develop and implement (as appropriate) regulatory and fiscal measures that promote healthy diets and physical activity. 2) To strengthen national and international collaboration amongst lawyers, regulatory bodies, policymakers, research institutions, civil society actors and communities to support regulatory and fiscal environments that promote healthy diets and physical activity. 3) To increase generation and use of relevant evidence and research from different disciplines to develop and implement effective regulatory and fiscal measures to promote healthy diets and physical activities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Government officials working in the ministries or agencies responsible for legislative and regulatory responses to non-communicable diseases (NCDs), academic institutions, patients&#x2019; groups, children&#x2019;s rights organisations, women&#x2019;s organisations, youth groups, labor groups, and faith communities, consumer organisations, and civil society organizations that are engaged in project activities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to strengthen national legislative, regulatory, and policy environments to promote healthy diets and physical activity.</narrative>
  </description>
